<TEXT>
a traveling president bush and his republican 
allies in the senate are working out details of a plan to salvage 
john towers nomination as defense secretary and bush has already 
begun lobbying from abroad 
the plan includes the possible rare public release of material 
culled from an fbi report on tower although bush said in tokyo he 
was anxious to protect the confidentiality of the people who agreed 
to talk to investigators 
senate republican leader bob dole said friday the white house is 
hoping to assemble a sanitized version of the report so senators 
can discuss in public the allegations against tower and their 
disposition 
dole said the hope is to produce a list of the charges and 
hopefully a list of the rebuttals so the american people will know 
that charge a was answered and is gone charge b etc 
tower has been struggling in his nomination fight against 
allegations of excessive drinking as well as womanizing and against 
an alleged conflict of interest stemming from the hundreds of 
thousands of dollars he received for work as a defense industry 
consultant 
in addition bush who returns monday from a fourday asian trip 
intends to meet individually with 10 or more democratic senators 
many of them conservative southerners to seek their votes 
ill do it personally and ill do it as forcefully as i can 
the president told reporters 
he said i will encourage people to look at the facts despite 
the talk about perceptions of towers problems 
thats not fair enough and thats not high enough a standard 
when it comes to the confirmation of an important nominee of this 
nature said bush a personal friend of tower for decades 
so i have made some calls and i will be talking to whoever 
remains open minded he said among the democrats to be called was 
sen lloyd bentsen a fellow texan and former senate colleague of 
towers 
bentsen said friday he was still uncommitted 
towers confirmation battle suffered a major defeat thursday 
night when the armed services committee on a strict party line roll 
call recommended 119 that the full senate reject the nomination 
democrats hold a 5545 majority in the full senate 
the partisan vote breakdown in committee heightened the dispute 
dramatically transforming it into a major test of the new 
republican presidents strength in a congress controlled by 
democrats 
among the democrats other than bentsen who said friday they 
remain uncommitted on the nomination were alabamas howell heflin 
and arizonas dennis deconcini the three are among the most 
conservative democrats in the senate and have been invited to the 
white house to meet with bush next week to discuss the nomination 
in his comments to reporters bush said there is no fallback 
there is no option and denied he was off to a late start with his 
personal lobbying its not too little too late 
the effort to release material gleaned by the fbis investigation 
is an attempt by republicans to prove their contention that despite 
the multitude of charges made against tower few if any can be 
corroborated 
release of the material would be a dramatic departure from the 
normal practice towers background check has been kept in a 
leadlined room on the fourthfloor of the capitol and senators are 
required to go there to read it 
in tokyo bush said confidentiality is vital but he added 
that senators should look at the report and make up their minds on 
the facts instead of perceptions 
with a full senate vote expected late next week dole gave a hint 
of the bruising struggle that lies ahead when he read for reporters 
high praise that sen sam nunn dga heaped upon tower shortly 
before the former texas senator retired from congress nunn is now 
chairman of the armed services committee and led the committee 
democrats in voting against confirmation 
dole also said a party line vote in the senate could be an end 
to the honeymoon for both georges that was a shot across the bow 
of sen george mitchell of maine the new majority leader 
but even as he said he hoped there was no party effort to line 
up every democrat against john tower he made it clear the issue 
is one of loyalty to the administration for the republicans 
this is the presidents first controversial vote and i think he 
has a right to expect all of us to support him he said 
</TEXT>
