magistrate joyce l alexander told walter f curran on friday 
notwithstanding family notwithstanding friends you might 
leave you have already done it once and you might do it again 
alexander said 
she noted that when the 46yearold boston man was caught at the 
canadian border in massena ny on feb 17 he had two passports 
an international drivers license a plane ticket to germany 
jewelry and the combination to a safe that has not been located 
curran persuaded clients to invest money in his personal account 
rather than through dean witter promising them 20 percent interest 
then converted the money to his own use assistant us attorney 
peter mullin said 
mullin said the broker also wrote six checks each for 125000 
to 500000 on overdrawn bank accounts 
the prosecutor said the investment and bank frauds involved a 
total dollar loss of between 2 million and 5 million 
defense attorney thomas troy said he would appeal alexanders 
decision 
curran is being held at the middlesex county jail if convicted 
he could be sentenced to up to 10 years in jail and a 500000 fine 
mullin said he could not predict when the case would come to 
trial but said it could take months 
</TEXT>
