<TEXT>
mahound is a businessman who decides to start a new religion in 
the city of jahilia only problem jahilia already has 360 gods and 
doesnt need another 
but the head of the ruling council proproses a deal if mahounds 
allah the islamic god will accept three of the local gods lat 
uzza and manat as archangels in his sect he can have his religion 
and also a seat on the council he takes the deal 
mahound appears in a dream sequence in the salman rushdie book 
the satanic verses he represents mohammed revered by moslems 
as the prophet who set down allahs revelations in the koran 
islams holy book and the novels portrayal of mahoundmohammed 
as a womanizer a moral coward willing to compromise his faith for 
general acceptance a conniving businessman who makes up laws to 
suit his own purposes has inflamed the islamic world 
the satanic verses is a dizzying 547page journey through 
countless plots subplots satire and philosophical questions 
lyrical scathing inquisitive and at times bewildering the 
novels subjects include societys preconceptions of good and evil 
the british treatment of illegal aliens the desire by indians to 
become assimilated in british culture and most notably the birth 
of the islamic faith 
rushdie a 41yearold native of bombay india who now lives in 
london writes in a streamofconsciousness style that leaves the 
reader alternately exhilirated bewildered and depending on ones 
religious and political orientation outraged 
the book opens with the bombing of a jumbo jet by terrorists two 
of the passengers gibreel farishta an indian actor who 
specializes in religious roles and saladin chamcha a radio star 
manage to survive by literally falling from the sky once they land 
gibreel assumes an angelic glow and saladin grows horns and 
hooves 
the books second fourth and sixth chapters mahound 
ayesha and return to jahilia contain the most controversial 
elements involving gibreels dream sequence 
during the dream mahound has a revelation in gibreels presence 
telling him to accept the deal but he soon learns that the 
supposedly divine message did not come from gibreel the archangel 
but from the devil who had been impersonating him 
mahound renounces the satanic verses he and his followers 
