<TEXT>
here is a chronology of the controversy over the satanic 
verses 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
sept 22 the satanic verses a 547page satirical fantasy 
that parodies some elements of moslem faith is published by viking 
penguin inc in england it is the sixth book for salman rushdie 
41 a bombayborn british citizen who has given up his moslem faith 
the novel wins him the whitbread novel award and critical acclaim 
oct 5 rushdies native india bans the book as blasphemous 
barring its import and sale and fears militant moslems may use it 
to incite riots rushdie protests the ban which later spreads to 
pakistan bangladesh egypt iran saudi arabia and other moslem 
countries 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
jan 14 about 1500 moslems in bradford england burn a copy 
of the book and protest its content wh smith and sons ltd pulls 
the book from its london stores despite the protests of rushdie and 
other writers 
feb 4 3000 moslems march against the book in birmingham 
england 
feb 12 six people die and 83 are injured as police fire 
semiautomatic weapons at 3000 fundamentalists who storm the us 
information center in islamabad pakistan demanding the book be 
banned in the united states sixtyfive people are arrested they 
burn the american flag and chant hang rushdie 
feb 13 police fire into a stonethrowing crowd protesting the 
book in srinagar india killing one person and wounding more than 
60 the mob forces shops and businesses to close moslem students 
also march in several pakistani cities 
feb 14 irans ayatollah ruhollah khomeini decrees a death 
sentence for rushdie whoever is killed doing this killing 
rushdie will be regarded as a martyr and will go directly to 
heaven khomeini tells wouldbe assassins rushdie says i wish 
i had written a more critical book scotland yard gives him police 
protection 
feb 15 rushdies 11city us tour coinciding with the us 
publication of the book is canceled after an iranian cleric puts a 
26 million price on his head the bounty is later doubled rushdie 
goes into hiding with his wife 
feb 16 waldenbooks the nations largest bookseller orders 
the 1995 book off its shelves out of fear that threats of violence 
might extend to its employees it sells the book on request the b 
dalton and barnes amp noble chains which have more than 1250 stores 
later pull the book from their shelves 
feb 18 rushdie says he regrets the distress that publication 
has occasioned but the iranian news agency says the apology isnt 
enough to rescind the death sentence khomeini tells moslems send 
him to hell 
feb 20 the 12 members of the european common market countries 
recall their ambassadors to iran britain which reopened its 
embassy in iran in november after a 17month break says it will 
close its operation again in tehran 
feb 21 iran retaliates by recalling all its ambassadors to the 
common market countries president bush says the call for rushdies 
execution is deeply offensive 
feb 22 hundreds of authors march outside the iranian mission 
to the united nations as outraged writers step up their protests 
over the reaction to the book you will have to kill us all 
says boston author james carroll in a remark aimed at khomeini b 
dalton and barnes amp noble reverse their decision to pull the book 
feb 24 in bombay india street protests against the novel 
left at least nine people dead and 40 injured initial news reports 
said up to 12 died in protests over the book but a police 
commissioner sm shangari said eight people died in the rioting 
and one man died later in the hospital peaceful protest also were 
reported in new delhi calcutta and several other indian cities 
feb 25 british foreign secretary sir geoffrey howe today said 
austria finland and a number of other countries he didnt 
identify have agreed to join the 12 common market nations in 
withdrawing their ambassadors from iran to protest tehrans death 
threat against rushdie 
 
</TEXT>
