here are some average ages of airline fleets 
from data compiled in january by avmark inc an appraisal and 
consulting company that keeps track of the worlds airliners 
the figures are based on the age of the fleets as of july 1 
1988 aviation experts say that more than chronological age the 
safety and value of an airliner is determined by the quality of 
maintenance and the number of flying cycles or takeoffs and 
landings and other factors in its individual history 
the average age of all us jetliners with major carriers is 
1267 years and the average age of the worldwide fleet of more than 
8800 airliners is 131 years 
