the center of the rolling cemetery grounds and later spoke with 
members of the local british community 
british war veterans and lawmakers decried the attendance of 
queen elizabeth iis husband at the funeral of the late monarch 
whom they denounced as a war criminal 
in london queen elizabeth ii on saturday appealed to one world 
war ii veteran to end his hunger strike which was begun in protest 
of philips attendance 
there was no immediate reaction to the latest appeal from 
70yearold andrew burgess who has been eating nothing and drinking 
only black tea for the last nine days 
fighting under hirohitos name japanese forces killed about 
27000 british soldiers and 20000 dutch troops many survivors also 
held hirohito accountable for atrocities committed against 127000 
dutch people interned during the war 
we are accustomed to hearing such kinds of criticism said 
seizaburo sato a professor of political science at tokyo 
university japan made a mistake 
but didnt the british or dutch do really bad things to 
asians they colonized for example india or indonesia if they 
think about what they have done for a much longer period of time 
than japan did i think they should be more modest 
most historians maintain that the late emperor was merely a 
glorified figurehead with little political power hirohito died on 
jan 7 at age 87 never having made clear his role in the war 
the cemetery is on the site of a playground that hirohito opened 
more than 65 years ago when he was crown prince 
nestled in the hills of yokohama south of tokyo the cemetery 
also holds the remains of soldiers from canada india new zealand 
