the countries wrapped up three days of talks in luanda angola 
that were held to discuss developments since the peace agreement was 
signed in new york in december 
under the usmediated treaty cuba has agreed to a phased 
withdrawal of its 50000 soldiers in angola who support the marxist 
government in its war against the national union for the total 
independence of angola guerrilla movement 
